SIMPLE: punctilious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Punctilious
<hw>Punc*til"ious</hw> <pr>(-y⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. It.
<ets>puntiglioso</ets>, Sp. <ets>puntilloso</ets>.]</ety> <def>Attentive
to punctilio; very nice or exact in the forms of behavior, etiquette, or
mutual intercourse; precise; exact in the smallest particulars.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>punctilious</xex> observance of divine laws.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Rogers.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Very <xex>punctilious</xex> copies of any
letters.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>The Nation.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Punctilious</qex> in the simple and intelligible instances of
common life.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Punc*til"ious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Punc*til"ious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Punction</ent>⟦br⟧
